      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 16 December 2004 vol 667 cc100-2WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_100ws' title='Col. 100WS &mdash; HL Deb 16 December 2004 vol 667 c100WS' name='column_100ws' href='#column_100ws' rel='bookmark'>100WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0667P0-09224'>
        <a name='S5LV0667P0_20041216_LWS_12'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-andrew-mcintosh' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0667P0_20041216_LWS_12' title='Link to this speech by Mr Andrew McIntosh' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-andrew-mcintosh" title="Mr Andrew McIntosh">Lord McIntosh of Haringey</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0667P0-09224">My honourable friend the Financial Secretary (Stephen Timms) has made the following Written Ministerial Statement.</p><a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_101ws' title='Col. 101WS &mdash; HL Deb 16 December 2004 vol 667 c101WS' name='column_101ws' href='#column_101ws' rel='bookmark'>101WS</a><p id="S5LV0667P0-09225">The Treasury has today published the Government's response to the consultation on the definition of home reversion type arrangements for inclusion in the scope of the Financial Services and
          <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_102ws' title='Col. 102WS &mdash; HL Deb 16 December 2004 vol 667 c102WS' name='column_102ws' href='#column_102ws' rel='bookmark'>102WS</a>
          <a href="/acts/markets-act-2000">Markets Act 2000</a>, which closed on 28 September 2004. Copies are available in the Vote Office and the Library of the House, and are accessible on the Treasury website at <span class="underline">www.hmtreasury.gov.uk</span>.</p>
        </blockquote>
